I was married to a Vietnam Veteran until last year, when he killed himself.  There was a great deal of stress in our lives last year - which I won't go into.  <br>
I thought he should stay with some friends for awhile.  He went and now I will never see him, touch him, hear his voice, just BE with him again - and neither will our daughter.<br>
I miss him and wish we would have done so many things differently - mainly TALK, LISTEN and COMFORT each other.  I have never known anyone who made me so happy and alive and who made me feel so loved.  I miss him more than I can say, yet, sometimes I feel angry with him for quitting.  I can't describe these emotions.<br>
A relative is a WWII vet, and he reminds me of him in some ways.  There's something in his eyes.  He knows somehow.<br>
I was wrong to push him away when we should have been holding on tighter than ever, but he didn't give me a chance to figure that out.  I only got one chance, and I should have paid attention.<br>

